This article is a Presidential Proclamation issued by President Barack Obama in 2011 to commemorate Veterans Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of honoring and supporting veterans and their families for their service and sacrifices in upholding America's ideals and protecting its freedom. It acknowledges the selflessness and dedication of service members and highlights their contributions to civilian life. The proclamation also calls for public ceremonies, private prayers, and patriotic activities to recognize the valor and sacrifice of veterans. It concludes by officially designating November 11th as Veterans Day and urging all Americans to participate in commemorative expressions and programs.